# ISSAC Assessment API — Response (score) endpoint
#
# How to get your nonce:
#   Option A: Browser console on any wp-admin page → wpApiSettings.nonce
#   Option B: wp eval 'echo wp_create_nonce("wp_rest");' --user=1

@baseUrl = https://issac.local/wp-json
@nonce = YOUR_NONCE_HERE

### Upsert a score for item 1.1
POST {{baseUrl}}/issac/v1/responses
Content-Type: application/json
X-WP-Nonce: {{nonce}}
Cookie: wordpress_logged_in_xxx=YOUR_COOKIE_HERE

{
  "item_code": "1.1",
  "score": 4
}

### Invalid score (expect 400)
POST {{baseUrl}}/issac/v1/responses
Content-Type: application/json
X-WP-Nonce: {{nonce}}
Cookie: wordpress_logged_in_xxx=YOUR_COOKIE_HERE

{
  "item_code": "1.1",
  "score": 6
}

### Invalid item code (expect 400)
POST {{baseUrl}}/issac/v1/responses
Content-Type: application/json
X-WP-Nonce: {{nonce}}
Cookie: wordpress_logged_in_xxx=YOUR_COOKIE_HERE

{
  "item_code": "99.99",
  "score": 3
}

# curl equivalent:
# curl -X POST "$BASE/wp-json/issac/v1/responses" \
#   -H "Content-Type: application/json" \
#   -H "X-WP-Nonce: $NONCE" \
#   --cookie "wordpress_logged_in_…=…" \
#   -d '{"item_code":"1.1","score":4}'
